body:
Normally when Running or Debugging Flutter tests I have no issues. When you click Run or Debug the test should start as expected. Recently, this started happening.

## Steps to Reproduce
Run a test in one of the following ways. (Using Run or Debug)
- Right Click menu after right clicking on code in a test file.
- Right Click menu after right clicking on a file in a test folder in Project view
- Right Click menu after right clicking on a test in the Run window (Test Results)

## Steps to NOT Reproduce (works correctly this way)
- Right Click menu after right clicking a test folder in Project view

comment_data.body: @jwren @DaveShuckerow I think new launch configs that are created via right-clicking and running on a test file are now defaulting to bazel launch configs. We should bisect this to verify, and if its the case, we'll want to address before the next release.

I'm able to see the following:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14947366/52435467-c7790880-2ac6-11e9-8214-22b9048dc22e.png)


The bazel run option is coming up above the pub run option.  I'll check that the bazel configuration factory knows to verify it's part of a bazel workspace before it provides any run configuration.
Thanks! Sounds good. There may also be an implicit ordering based on the order they're declared in plugin.xml, but I haven't verified that.

Just a note I am seeing this behaviour inconsistently. Sometimes it will only show the bazel option, sometimes only pub, sometimes both.

Here is an example video of the behaviour being inconsistent.

https://drive.google.com/open?id=1BE9frMPJKxxfgOZo2PJm5qEWH4KN1L3E
@MisterJimson can you show an example of where you would see both options?
Sure let me see. I definitely have seen it doing the same things I did in the that video.

Here is a good one. You can see me clicking in the exact same test and file but getting different results back to back.

https://drive.google.com/open?id=1li7TNoSrrwV017xczFBVyFnEQnf08CxE
I'm still getting this error today. @MisterJimson Did you manage to fix it?
This is resolved for me as of the 33.0.1 release.
Thanks @MisterJimson I updated to 33.0.1 and it is solved also. Cheers!

just for anyone coming to this now, i tried to run my tests and was greeted with this error i then updated flutter but still had this error i had to delete my test file and create a new one and then everything is awesome

title: Running/Debugging tests gives error "No Bazel target set"
